friend Sweater</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">or possibly, the easiest sweater you\'ll ever knit!</h4>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">An Original Design by Jane Nickerson</h5></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" id="8b8a-6286-68a6-4921" style="display: block; position: relative; opacity: 1; left: 0px; top: 0px;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526302314knitfitco sm Boyfriend LS Front.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="b90e-c6e2-d9ad-0f91" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="fe47-2e49-1984-ae31">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248"><h2 id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248"><strong>Description:</strong></h2>\r\n<table id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>The Boyfriend Sweater is a true classic; it is extremely comfortable and not at all fussy! The pattern is written for standard sizing plus one inch of ease for a relaxed fit. However, if you would like to customize the fit, you should consider “The Girlfriend Sweater… a slightly fitted version of the easiest sweater you\'ll ever knit!”</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248"><strong>Sizes:</strong></h2>\r\n<table id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>This sweater has been created for you, [[FIRST_NAME]] [[LAST_NAME]], with your measurements.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 id="a2ff-9254-e110-5248"><strong>Gauge:</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The original design was created in a gauge of 5.5 stitches and 7 rows per inch in stockinette. However, you can select a yarn from fingering to aran weight if you’d like. Just make sure that you have knit an accurate gauge swatch in the yarn you will be using.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note: To measure a proper gauge, cast on 40 stitches using the needle size recommended for the yarn. Knit in Stockinette for at least 4 inches. Take swatch off the needles, lay it flat and measure in the center towards the top of the swatch. Knit using suggested needles first. Adjust needle size until you have a swatch that feels soft and drapey without being too loose. </span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Materials:</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Knit a gauge swatch with your favorite yarn and use the table below to estimate the amount of yarn required.</p>\r\n<p>NOTE: It is always smart to have a little extra, so if in doubt, buy and extra skein!</p></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" style="display: block;" id="ada5-7bfa-01b0-0cbf">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1559486195Long Sweater Yarn Yardage Table.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="c12b-38bc-146a-2a3a" rel="" style="width: 100%;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" id="e4c6-f1d9-be3f-06a5" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="6535-d4fb-01f8-9928"><h3 id="6535-d4fb-01f8-9928"><strong>Designer’s Note:</strong></h3>\r\n<p id="6535-d4fb-01f8-9928"></p>\r\n<table id="6535-d4fb-01f8-9928">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>This sweater is meant to be oversized and casual. Wear it over leggings or your favorite jeans. Lounge on the couch or shop at the farmers’ market!</p>\r\n<p>The only measurements you need are circumference - bust or hips, whichever is larger; and, length to underarm: How long do you want the sweater? Tunic over leggings? Or lower hip...it’s up to you!</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Directions:</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span>Cast on [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON]]</span><span>&nbsp;stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Join in the round, being careful not to twist the stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Work in a knit 1, purl 1 rib for </span><span>[[LENGTH_OF_RIBBING]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Place markers at the beginning of the round and at </span><span>the half way around.</span></p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>Knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]] </span><span>inches from the lower </span>edge to the underarm.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h3><strong>Neckline Shaping</strong></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Front</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue </span><span>to knit the front and shape armholes as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span style="font-size: 11px;"> </span><span style="font-size: 11px;">[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] </span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off <span style="font-size: 11px;">[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] </span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 11px;"> [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end <span style="font-size: 11px;"> [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]] </span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. </span></p>\r\n<p><span>At the same time, place a marker at the center.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2nd row: Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Turn. Put right front shoulder stitches on a holder.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h3><b>Left Front Shaping:</b></h3>\r\n<p><span>Continue to shape the v-neck while knitting straight at </span><span>the armhole edge:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit to 3 stitches from the end, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight at armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck </span><span>edge every other row until there are </span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]] </span>stitches remaining and the armhole depth equals [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches.</p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]] </span><span>stitches at the beginning of the next right side row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at the beginning </span>of the next row.</p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h3><b>Right Front Shaping:</b></h3>\r\n<p><span>Place right front stitches back on the needle and attach </span>yarn to the right side at the neck edge.</p>\r\n<p><span>Shape neckline as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>K1, k2tog, knit to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the neck edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge every other row until there are </span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]] <span>stitches remaining.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight until armhole depth measures [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]] </span><span>stitches at the beginning of the next wrong side row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at the </span><span>beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Back</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the needle.</span></p>\r\n<p>Bind off <span style="font-size: 11px;">[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] </span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off <span style="font-size: 11px;">[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] </span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 11px;"> [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 11px;"> [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span style="font-size: 11px;"> [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]] </span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. At the same time, place a marker at the center.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight until armhole depth equals [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]] stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_3]] stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off center stitches.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable active" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="dae3-1d99-95e0-685d">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="53ff-0df4-9cba-d86e"><h3><strong>Sleeves</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Cast on [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON_FOR_SLEEVE]] </span><span>stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>K2, p2 rib for 8 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Begin stockinette stitch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_FOREARM_INCREASES]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_UPPER_ARM_INCREASES]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight until the sleeve measures</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[ARM_LENGTH_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Sleeve Cap Shaping:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Bind off </span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</p>\r\n<p>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 each side every other row&nbsp;<span>[[DEC_1_STITCH_EVERY_OTHER_ROW_X_TIMES]]</span>times.</p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 2 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_2_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 4 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_4_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[BO_REMAINING_1]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Finishing</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Sew the front and back together at the shoulders. Starting at shoulder, pick up and knit an even number of stitches at the rate of about [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches per inch around the neck, placing a marker at the center front.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Work a knit 1, purl 1 rib for [[LENGTH_OF_NECK_EDGE_RIBBING]] inches around the neck as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Beginning at the shoulder, knit in rib to 2 stitches before the front center v marker, k2tog, sm, p, sm, ssk, knit in rib to beginning of round.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off loosely. Sew the side and sleeve seams.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Pin the sleeves into the armhole, lining up the top of the sleeve cap with the shoulder seam and the underarm seams of the sleeve and the sweater. Sew the armhole in, easing curve of the sleeve cap as you sew.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Weave in all loose ends.</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span></p></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                    \r\n                <div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" id="0c62-880c-8990-014c" style="display: block; position: relative; opacity: 1; left: 0px; top: 0px;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526303945Boyfriend LS Side mini.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="6338-8357-99e1-6c52" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	(3, NULL, 8, '<div class="container">\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526132035Untitled drawing (28).jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="aa4d-3751-bfe0-c90c" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12">\r\n            <h2 id="679c-b0a5-ad4c-3cf9" style="text-align: center;">\r\n                Marsha’s Lacey Tee\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <h3 id="679c-b0a5-ad4c-3cf9" style="text-align: center;">\r\n                An Original Design by Jane Nickerson\r\n            </h3>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526417098Lacey P Front knit fit template.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="cbc7-4cee-6637-cac6" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h2 id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Description:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <table id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    The light and airy mesh lace adds a delicate border and bodice to this summer tee. It can be knit in cotton, linen, rayon, bamboo or any combination for a cool summer top. The longer length is slimming and fashionable over slender or wide-legged pants.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h3 id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Sizes:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    This sweater has been created for [[FIRST_NAME]] [[LAST_NAME]] with your measurements.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h3 id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Gauge:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    This pattern has been written for a gauge of [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches and [[ROW_GAUGE]] rows per inch.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    The original design was created in a gauge of 6 stitches and 8 rows per inch in stockinette. However, you can select a yarn from fingering to aran weight if you’d like. Just make sure that you have knit an accurate gauge swatch in the yarn you will be using.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Note: To measure a proper gauge, cast on 40 stitches using the needle size recommended for the yarn. Knit in Stockinette for at least 4 inches. Take swatch off the needles, lay it flat and measure in the center towards the top of the swatch. Knit using suggested needles first. Adjust needle size until you have a swatch that feels soft and drapey without being too loose.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h3 id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Materials:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table id="11d6-5ffc-77e0-7dc4">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yarn estimated for sizes 32 (34, 36, 38, 40, 42, 44)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        Fingering weight yarn, size 4 circular 24” or 32” needles, US E crochet hook\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed: 700 (750, 800, 900, 950, 1050, 1100)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        DK weight yarn, size 6 circular 24” or 32” needles, &nbsp;US F crochet hook\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed: 650 (700, 750, 800, 850, 900, 950)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        Worsted weight yarn, size 7 &nbsp;circular 24” or 32” needles, US G crochet hook\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed: 550 (600, 650, 700, 800, 850, 950)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    2 24” to 32” circular needles as indicated by the weight of the yarn used.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1 Needle one size larger than used for the tee (used for the 3 needle bind-off).\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Crochet Hook as indicated by the weight of the yarn used.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    2 Stitch Markers\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h3 id="cc47-3959-15b6-c8be">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Designer’s Notes:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table id="cc47-3959-15b6-c8be">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    As a rule, when I design a sleeveless top,&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    I use a round of single crochets around the neck and&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    sleeve openings. This creates a smooth, non-rolling finished edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <b>\r\n                                    Abbreviations:\r\n                                </b>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <table>\r\n                                <tbody>\r\n                                    <tr>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 419.062px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    BO - Bind Off\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 400.812px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    M1l - Make one left by knitting into\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    the stitch below the next stitch\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                    </tr>\r\n                                    <tr>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 419.062px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    CO - Cast On\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 400.812px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    M1r - Make one right by knitting into the\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitch 2 stitches below the stitch just knit\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                    </tr>\r\n                                    <tr>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 419.062px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    K2tog - knit the next 2 stitches together\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 400.812px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Sl1-k2tog-psso - Slip one stitch, knit the\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    next 2 stitches together, and pass the\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    slipped stitch over the 2 just knit together\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                    </tr>\r\n                                    <tr>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 419.062px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Ssk - slip the next 2 stitches purlwise and knit them together through the back loop\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                        <td style="width: 400.812px;">\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Yo - bring the yarn to the front and over\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    the needle with the next stitch, creating\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    a new stitch\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                    </tr>\r\n                                </tbody>\r\n                            </table>\r\n                            <h2>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Directions:\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h2>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Using a provisional cast on method,\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                CO [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON]]&nbsp;stitches.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Join in the round, being careful not to twist the stitches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            Knit 1 round.\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Work the English Mesh pattern as follows:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Round 1:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    *K1,( yo, k1) twice, sl1-k2 tog-psso*\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Round 2 and even rows: knit.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Round 3:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    *Ssk, k1, k2 tog, yo, k1, yo*\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Round 5:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    *Sl1-k2 tog-psso, k1,( yo, k1) twice*\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Continue in English mesh for 5 inches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <table>\r\n                                <tbody>\r\n                                    <tr>\r\n                                        <td>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                Knit in stockinette, decreasing every\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[DECREASE_EVERY_N_ROWS_WAIST]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    rounds to the waist as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Round 1:&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    K1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches before the side marker, ssk,&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                k1, sm, k1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches before the beginning\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    of round marker, ssk, k1, sm.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Rounds 2 -&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[DECREASE_EVERY_N_ROWS_WAIST]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                : Knit around.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                Repeat these rounds for a total of\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_WAIST]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                times.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_WAIST]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                inches from the lower edge.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <h3>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Bust Shaping\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h3>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    You may be increasing at different rates in front and&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                in back depending on your fit. Read the following 2\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    sections before you begin.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Round 1: K1, m1r, knit to 1 stitch before the side marker,&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                m1l, k1, sm, k1, m1r, knit to 1 stitch before the beginning\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    of round marker, m1l, k1, sm.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Increase from the waist&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <b>\r\n                                                    in front\r\n                                                </b>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[TEXT_FOR_BUST_INCREASES_FRONT]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;inches.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    At the same time, increase from the waist\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                in back\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[TEXT_FOR_BACK_INCREASES]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;inches.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <h3>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Underarm Shaping\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h3>\r\n                                            <h4>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Front\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h4>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue to&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    knit the front and shape armholes as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                Bind off\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <h3>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Neckline Shaping\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h3>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Decrease 1 stitch at each end as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    2nd row: Purl back, and place a marker at the center.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Turn. Put right front shoulder stitches on a holder.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <h4>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Left Front Shaping:\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h4>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Row 1: K1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches from the neck&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    edge, ssk, k1.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Row 2: Purl to the armhole edge.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Repeat rows 1 and 2 until you have decreased one stitch at the armhole edge a total of&nbsp;[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    times.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    every other row for a total of 4 times. Then decrease every&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                4 rows until there are\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitches remaining and the armhole depth equals [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                inches.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitches at the beginning of the next right side row.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Purl back.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Purl back.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <h4>\r\n                                                <strong>\r\n                                                    Right Front Shaping:\r\n                                                </strong>\r\n                                            </h4>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Place right front stitches back on the needle and attach&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                yarn to the right side at the neck edge.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Shape neckline as follows:\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Row 1: K1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches from the armhole&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                edge, ssk, k1.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Row 2: Purl to the neck edge.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Repeat rows 1 and 2 until you have decreased one&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitch at the armhole edge a total of&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                times.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    edge every other row until there are&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                [[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitches remaining.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Knit straight until armhole depth measure [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                inches.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    stitches at the beginning of the next wrong side row.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Knit back.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]]&nbsp;\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                                stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Knit back.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                            <p>\r\n                                                <span>\r\n                                                    Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                                </span>\r\n                                            </p>\r\n                                        </td>\r\n                                    </tr>\r\n                                </tbody>\r\n                            </table>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526560690Lacey LS Side sm knitfit.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="360a-9751-30c9-0f6d" rel="" style="width: 100%;">\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" id="4d92-9733-e660-5765">\r\n                <div class="view" id="acdc-d436-6dc5-5e4f">\r\n                    <h3>\r\n                        <strong>\r\n                            Back\r\n                        </strong>\r\n                    </h3>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Repeat armhole shaping as for front.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Knit straight until armhole depth measure&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]]&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                        <span>\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_3]] stitches at the&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        beginning of the 2 rows.\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Bind off center stitches.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <h3>\r\n                        <strong>\r\n                            Sleeves\r\n                        </strong>\r\n                    </h3>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            The sleeves are also knit in the round. You may use the&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Magic Loop, two circular or double pointed needles.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Using a provisional cast on method,&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        CO [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON_FOR_SLEEVE]]\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            &nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            stitches.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Join in the round, being careful not to twist the stitches.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Work the English Mesh pattern as follows:\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Round 2 and even rows: knit\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Round 3: *K1,( yo, k1) twice, sl1-k2 tog-psso*\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Round 5: *Ssk, k1, k2 tog, yo, k1, yo*\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Round 7: *Sl1-k2 tog-psso, k1,( yo, k1) twice*\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Continue in English mesh for 3 inches.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            Knit in stockinette until the sleeve measures&nbsp;\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        <span>\r\n                            [[LENGTH_ELBOW_TO_UNDER_ARM_LESS_1]] inches.\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h4 id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Sleeve Cap Shaping\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h4>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                &nbsp;\r\n                <span>\r\n                    stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                Decrease 1 stitch at each end\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                times as follows:\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    2nd row: Purl back.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Knit [[NO_OF_ROWS_TO_KNIT_STRAIGHT]]\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;rows.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Decrease 1 each side every other row&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[DEC_1_STITCH_EVERY_OTHER_ROW_X_TIMES]]&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    times as follows: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off 2 stitches at the beginning of the next [[BO_2_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]]\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;rows.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off 4 stitches at the beginning of the next&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[BO_4_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] rows.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[BO_REMAINING_1]]\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;stitches at the beginning of&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                the next row.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                [[BO_REMAINING_2]] stitches at the beginning of\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    the next row.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Bind off remaining [[BO_REMAINING_3]]\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    &nbsp;stitches.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <h2 id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Finishing\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Sew the shoulder seams together. Block the sweater&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    before finishing the neckline.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p id="e25d-e00f-660b-e286">\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Using a crochet hook as indicated by the weight of the yarn&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    you are using, attach the yarn at the shoulder seam and&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    crochet a single crochet stitch at the rate of&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches per inch around the neckline.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Join at the top of the first single crochet stitch and fasten\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    .\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>', '<div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                 