                  </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="2e60-e2dd-b7af-c443">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="ad38-3354-e33a-0958"><h2 id="8a7b-98ec-ddf7-a0cc">Description:</h2>\r\n<table id="8a7b-98ec-ddf7-a0cc">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>This pattern has been created specifically for you, [[FIRST_NAME]] [[LAST_NAME]], with your measurements.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Emily’s Sweater is your opportunity to knit a sweater that truly fits! Not only is this pattern written for your measurements, but you can choose from 4 different levels of fit within the custom pattern. Each fit is described below, and the pattern leads you to customize this very feminine, all season top.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>This sweater can be knit in dk or worsted weight yarn. The orange sample is knit in Cascade Venezia worsted; the brown sample is knit in Cascade Ultrapima Cotton dk.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><br><br></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3 id="8a7b-98ec-ddf7-a0cc">Materials:</h3>\r\n<table id="8a7b-98ec-ddf7-a0cc">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><br>\r\n<p><span>For approximate sizes: 32 (36, 40, 44)</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Worsted weight yarn 1095 (1314, 1314, 1530) yds</span></p>\r\n<p><span>24” or 32” US 7 needles or size required to make gauge</span></p>\r\n<p><span>or</span></p>\r\n<p><span>DK weight yarn 1241 (1542, 1542, 1788)</span></p>\r\n<p><span>24” or 32” US 6 needles or size required to make gauge</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Note: The body of the sweater is knit in the round. 32” circular needles are best in most cases.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>4 stitch markers</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="e25f-0c7f-1f27-bab6">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><h3 id="8998-4b19-4704-7363">Gauge:</h3>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><span>This pattern has been written for a gauge of [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches and [[ROW_GAUGE]] rows per inch.</span></p>\r\n<h3 id="8998-4b19-4704-7363">Abbreviations and Techniques:</h3>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><span>Abbreviations and symbols used in the lace pattern are listed with the lace chart.</span></p>\r\n<h3 id="8998-4b19-4704-7363">Determining Fit and Measure:</h3>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><span>You have a choice to make before starting this pattern. How closely do you want this sweater to fit? It is designed in 4 different fits:</span></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><b>Casual Fit:</b><span>&nbsp;For those of us that no longer have the hourglass shape of youth, the casual fit is knit straight up from hip to shoulder. It maintains the feminine neckline and lacy sleeve, but has a casual and modest&nbsp;</span><span>outline.</span></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><b>Soft Shaping Fit:<span>&nbsp;</span></b><span>This is a very forgiving, yet feminine silhouette. A panel of ribbing underneath the arm adds “negative ease” which means that the sweater will cling to your body. If you want less “cling,” add one inch to your measurements so that the sweater can skim over your curves. This is a good choice for a small busted, thin woman.</span></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><b>Very Shapely Fit:</b><span>&nbsp;Add increases and decreases designed to follow your curves to the soft shaping of the ribbed side panel. You will be measuring not only your hips, waist and bust, but the rate of increase and decrease, and shaping the front and back of the sweater to follow your curves. This fit is NOT for the faint of heart, but will look amazing on a youthful figure. Again, you can add an inch to your measurement so that the sweater is not too tight.</span></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"></p>\r\n<p id="8998-4b19-4704-7363"><b>Better than Classic Fit:<span>&nbsp;</span></b><span>Remove the ribbed panel, but follow the instructions for the Very Shapely Fit. The sweater will fit you perfectly without the cling.</span></p>\r\n<h2 id="8998-4b19-4704-7363">Directions:</h2>\r\n<p><span>Cast on [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON]] stitches and join in the round being careful not to twist the stitches.</span></p>\r\n<h4>Work a Disappearing Rib pattern as follows:</h4>\r\n<p><span><strong>For Very Shapely and Soft Shaping Fits:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rows 1-3: &nbsp;K1, p1 rib for 11 stitches. Place a marker. Continue in rib pattern for [[SIDE_MARKER_LESS_SIDE_PANEL]] stitches. pm, knit 22 in rib, pm. Knit K1, P1 rib to 11 stitches before the end of round, pm. Continue in rib pattern to end of round.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rows 4-5: Continue in rib pattern to 1st marker. Sm, k3, p1 to next marker. Sm, k1, p1 to next marker. Sm, k3, p1 to next marker. Sm, k1, p1 to end of round.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rows 6-7: Continue in k1, p1 rib pattern to 1st marker. Sm, k7, p1 to next marker. Sm, k1, p1 to next marker. Sm, k7, p1 to next marker. Sm, k1, p1 to end of round.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span><strong>For Casual and Better than Classic Fits:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rows 1-3: K1, p1 rib around, placing markers at the beginning of round and at the halfway point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span><span>Rows 4-5: K3, p1 around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span><span>Rows 6-7: K7, p1 around.</span></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Knitting the Body of the Sweater</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Row 8: Begin main body pattern as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><b>For Casual Fit:<span>&nbsp;</span></b><span>Continue to knit in stockinette until you have knit [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches. Then proceed to Armhole Shaping.</span></p>\r\n<p><b>Soft Shaping Fit:<span>&nbsp;</span></b><span>Knit in rib pattern to first marker. Knit in stockinette to second marker. Knit in rib pattern to third marker. Knit in stockinette to fourth marker. Complete the round in rib pattern. Continue in this way until you have knit [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches. Then proceed to Armhole Shaping.</span></p>\r\n<p><b>Better than Classic Fit:<span>&nbsp;</span></b><span>Follow the Waist Shaping instructions below. Knit in stockinette around, incorporating the decreases, until you have knit [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_WAIST]] inches. Then proceed to Bust Shaping.</span></p>\r\n<p><b>For Very Shapely Fit: &nbsp;</b><span>Follow the Waist Shaping instructions below, incorporating waist decreases while you knit in rib pattern to first marker, knit in stockinette to second marker, knit in rib pattern to third marker, and knit in stockinette to fourth marker. Complete the round in rib pattern. Continue until you have knit [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_WAIST]] inches. Then proceed to Bust Shaping.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>WAIST SHAPING</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>Design Note:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Most sweater patterns are designed to fit someone\'s idea of the “standard” woman. &nbsp;However, few of us fit that standard. Some of us are “long-waisted” and some of us are “short-waisted” (or “petite”). This is an important distinction at this point in the pattern because the shaping should follow YOUR body style.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Look in the mirror and decide how to best decrease to your waist based on your shape. I happen to have square hips, which means that I have to knit straight for 2 ½ inches before I even begin to decrease for my waist. Then I have to decrease quickly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>For example: I\'ve knit 2 ½ inches before beginning the decrease (my hips are pretty square). You may be long-waisted or need a slower decrease to match the curve of your waist.</span></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Knitting the Waist Shaping Decreases:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Decrease every [[DECREASE_EVERY_N_ROWS_WAIST]] rounds to the waist as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>For Very Shapely Fit:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Round 1: Knit the negative ease side panel in the k1, p1 pattern, sm, k2tog, knit to 2 stitches before the negative ease panel marker, ssk, sm, knit the negative ease side panel in the k1, p1 pattern past the side marker to the &nbsp;next marker, sm, k2tog, knit to 2 stitches before the next marker, ssk, k1, sm.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rounds 2 - [[DECREASE_EVERY_N_ROWS_WAIST]]: Knit around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Repeat these rounds for a total of [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_WAIST]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>For the Better than Classic Fit:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Round 1: K1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches before the first marker, ssk, k1, sm, k1, k2tog, knit to 3 stitches before the side marker, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rounds 2 - [[DECREASE_EVERY_N_ROWS_WAIST]]: Knit around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Repeat these rounds for a total of [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_WAIST]] times.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>BUST SHAPING</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>You may be increasing at different rates in front and in back depending on your fit. Read the following 2 sections before you begin.</span></p>\r\n<p><b>For the Better than Classic Fit:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>You will likely be Increasing in the front more often than in the back. The method for increasing is as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Round 1: (Increase in front) K1, m1r, knit to 1 stitch before the side marker, m1l, k1, sm, (increase in back) k1, m1r, knit to 1 stitch before the beginning of round marker, m1l, k1, sm.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Increase from the waist&nbsp;</span><b>in front</b><span>&nbsp;at this rate:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rounds 2 - [[NO_OF_ROWS_BETWEEN_INCREASES_BUST]]: Knit around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Repeat rounds 1 - [[NO_OF_ROWS_BETWEEN_INCREASES_BUST]] for a total of [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_INCREASE_BUST]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]</span><span>&nbsp;inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>At the same time, increase from the waist&nbsp;</span><b>in back</b><span>&nbsp;at this rate:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_INCREASE_BACK]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]</span><span>&nbsp;inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>For the Very Shapely Fit:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Round 1: (Increase in front) Knit the negative ease side panel in the k1, p1 pattern, sm, m1, knit to 1 stitch before the negative ease panel marker, m1, sm, knit the negative ease side panel in the k1, p1 pattern past the side marker to the &nbsp;next marker, (increase in back) sm, k1, m1, knit to 1 stitch before the next marker, m1, k1, sm.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Rounds 2 - [[NO_OF_ROWS_BETWEEN_INCREASES_BUST]]: &nbsp;Knit around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Repeat these rounds for a total of [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_INCREASE_BUST]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>At the same time, increase from the waist&nbsp;</span><b>in back</b><span>&nbsp;as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_INCREASE_BACK]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]</span><span>&nbsp;inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Armhole Shaping</strong></h3>\r\n<p><b>For Very Shapely and Soft Shaping Fits:</b><span>&nbsp;Continue with the rib pattern throughout the armhole shaping process. As you decrease for the armhole, the ribbed stitches will be bound off and you will continue to knit the front and back in stockinette.</span></p>\r\n<p><span></span></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Underarm Shaping</strong></h4>\r\n<p><b>Front</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue to knit the front and shape armholes as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span>&nbsp;stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;</span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2nd row: Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>Shape Front Neckline:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Count the stitches remaining, and divide in half = _____. This is the number of stitches to bind off in the center.</span><span><br></span><span>Shape as follows: Knit 1/4 of the stitches.</span><span><br></span><span></span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off the center stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit to end.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>Right Front:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Place 1st set of stitches on a holder, and work on the right front neckline.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Purl to 3 stitches before the neck edge, p2tog, p1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 2: K1, k2tog, knit to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Repeat rows 1 and 2 one more time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit in stockinette until the armhole depth measures [[ARMHOLE_DEPTH]]</span><span>&nbsp;ending with a purl row facing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Bind off one half of the remaining stitches. Purl to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 2: Knit to end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 3: Bind off remaining stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><b>Left Front:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Put the left front stitches back on the needle, attaching the yarn to the purl side.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Purl 1, p2togtbl, purl to the end</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 2: Knit to 3 stitches from the center, ssk, k1.</span><span><br></span><span>Repeat rows 1 and 2 one more time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit in stockinette until the armhole measures [[ARMHOLE_DEPTH]]</span><span>&nbsp;ending with a knit row facing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Bind off one half of the stitches, &nbsp;knit to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 2: Purl to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 3: Bind off remaining stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Back:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue to knit the front and shape armholes as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span>&nbsp;<span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;</span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2nd row: Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit in stockinette until the armhole measures [[ARMHOLE_DEPTH]]</span><span>&nbsp;ending with a knit row facing.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>Shape Back Neck:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Count the remaining stitches. _____ Note the number of shoulder stitches counted for the front shoulder stitches. Multiply that number x 2 ______. Subtract the left and right shoulder stitches from the remaining stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Remaining stitches _____ - Shoulder stitches ____ = Back Neck stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Knit right shoulder stitches. Bind off &nbsp;Back neck stitches. Knit to end.</span><span><br></span><span>Row 2: Bind off ½ left shoulder stitches. Purl to end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 3: Knit to end</span><span><br></span><span>Row 4: Bind off remaining stitches.</span><span><br></span><span><br></span><span>Attach yarn to Left shoulder at neck edge.</span><span><br></span><span>Row 1: Purl to end.</span><span><br></span><span>Row 2: Bind off ½ left shoulder stitches. Knit to end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 3: Purl to end.</span><span><br></span><span>Row 4: Bind off remaining stitches.</span><span><br></span></p>\r\n<p></p></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable active" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="a76d-2edd-166b-9877">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="2236-9eb1-f15f-c8db"><h3><strong>SLEEVES</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Cast on<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON_FOR_SLEEVE]]</span><span>&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;stitches, placing a marker after<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_STITCH_MARKER]]&nbsp;</span>stitches and after<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_STITCH_MARKER]] stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p>Rows 1-3: *k1, p1* across.</p>\r\n<p><span>Row 4: Purl to the marker, sm, p25 (lace panel), sm, p to end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 5: Begin lace pattern at Row 2 of the lace pattern.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>The lace pattern is worked over 16 rows. Write down which rows on each pattern repeat you will be increasing and refer back to it as you knit the sleeve.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>For example, increasing every 10 rows would look like this:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Lace Repeat 1: row 4; Lace Repeat 1: row 14;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Lace Repeat 2: row 8;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Lace Repeat 3: row 2; repeat 3: 12; 4: 6; 4:16; 5:10; 6:4; 6:14.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>You will be increasing on the sleeve as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit 1, m1r, knit across in pattern to the last stitch. M1l, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_FOREARM_INCREASES]]</span><span>&nbsp;Continue to knit in lace pattern until the sleeve measures [[WRIST_TO_ELBOW]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_UPPER_ARM_INCREASES]]</span><span> Continue to knit in lace pattern until the sleeve measures [[ARM_LENGTH_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Lace Pattern:</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Row 1: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 2: k2, yo, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k1, yo, yo, yo, yo, k1, k2tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k1, yo, ssk, yo, ssk, k1, yo, yo, yo, yo, k1, ssk, yo, ssk, yo, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 3: P7, k1, p1, k1, p12, k1, p1, k1, p8</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 4: k2, yo, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k4, k3tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k3, yo, ssk, yo, s1 k2tog psso, k4, ssk, yo, ssk, yo, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 5: purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 6: k2, yo, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k2, k3tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k5, yo, ssk, yo, s1 k2tog psso, k2, ssk, yo, ssk, yo, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 7: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 8: k2, yo, k2tog, yo, k2tog, k3tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k3, yo, ssk, k2, yo, ssk, yo, s1 k2tog psso, ssk, yo, ssk, yo, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 9: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 10: k2, yo, k2tog, k3tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k2, k2tog, yo, k1, yo, ssk, k2, yo, ssk, yo, s1 k2tog psso, ssk, yo, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 11: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 12: k3, k2tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k2, k2tog, yo, k3, yo, ssk, k2, yo, ssk, yo, ssk, k3</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 13: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 14: k2, k2tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k2, k2tog, yo, k1, yo, s1 k2tog psso, yo, k1, yo, ssk, k2, yo, ssk, yo, ssk, k2</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 15: Purl</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Row 16: k1, k2tog, yo, k2tog, yo, k4, yo, k3tog, yo, k1, yo, &nbsp;s1 k2tog psso, yo, k4, yo, ssk, yo, ssk, k1</span></p></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" style="display: block;" id="982a-46d5-87ea-e93b">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1527005705Emily\'s Lace Diagram.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="b3c2-d07e-2612-20ca" rel="" style="width: 100%;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" style="display: block;" id="d850-6183-da5c-7c33">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1527005410Emily\'s Lace Key.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="cda5-a541-49e8-c4ca" rel="" style="width: 100%;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="2192-9816-c986-eae0">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="4387-7130-9671-a901"><h3><strong>Sleeve Cap Shaping</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Continue to knit lace pattern while shaping the sleeve cap. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span><span>&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;</span><span>times as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2nd row: Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit [[NO_OF_ROWS_TO_KNIT_STRAIGHT]]&nbsp;rows.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Decrease 1 each side every other row [[DEC_1_STITCH_EVERY_OTHER_ROW_X_TIMES]]&nbsp;</span><span>times as follows: K1, k2tog, knit in pattern to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 2 stitches at the beginning of the next [[BO_2_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Stop the lace pattern here, and knit across in stockinette for the remainder of the sleeve cap.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 4 stitches at the beginning of the next [[BO_4_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[BO_REMAINING_1]]</span><span>&nbsp;stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[BO_REMAINING_2]]</span><span>&nbsp;stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off remaining [[BO_REMAINING_3]]</span><span>&nbsp;stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><br><br></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Finishing</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span>Block the sleeve flat before sewing the seam together.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Sew shoulders together and block the body.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Attach the sleeves.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>Neckline</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Using the gauge of the yarn you are using ( [[STITCH_GAUGE]] 