	(6, NULL, 11, '<div class="container">\r\n    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12">\r\n            <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526132035Untitled drawing (28).jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="6272-66f2-1ecb-e36f" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12">\r\n            <h2 style="text-align: center;">\r\n                Trevor’s V-Necked Sweater\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <h4 style="text-align: center;">\r\n                Design by Jane Nickerson\r\n            </h4>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526562110Trevor and Angel.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="efa6-45f5-0c31-7584" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h2>\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Description:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <p>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    If he’s anything like mine, your son wants a comfortable, no fuss sweater. This is a true classic, with just enough pattern to make it an interesting but not complicated knit. The pattern is written for standard sizing plus one inch of ease for a relaxed fit. If your guy is a “Hipster”, you might try a “Shapely Fit” for a tighter sweater. However, you can specify “Casual” for a more loose fit.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h3>\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Sizes:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    This sweater has been created for you, [[FIRST_NAME]] [[LAST_NAME]], with your measurements.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <h3>\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Gauge:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    This pattern has been written for a gauge of [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches and [[ROW_GAUGE]] rows per inch.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    The original design was created in a gauge of 4 stitches and 5 rows per inch in stockinette. However, you can select a yarn from fingering to aran weight if you’d like. Just make sure that you have knit an accurate gauge swatch in the yarn you will be using.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Note: To measure a proper gauge, cast on 40 stitches using the needle size recommended for the yarn. Knit in Stockinette for at least 4 inches. Take swatch off the needles, lay it flat and measure in the center towards the top of the swatch. Knit using suggested needles first. Adjust needle size until you have a swatch that feels soft and drapey without being too loose.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h3 id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Materials:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h3>\r\n            <table id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1 - 24 or 32” Circular needle in the size used to knit the gauge swatch.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1 - 24 or 32” Circular needle in the size 2 sizes smaller than that used to knit the gauge swatch.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    8 - stitch markers\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    2 - stitch markers different from the 8 for side markers.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yarn estimated for sizes 32 (34, 36, 38, 40, 42, 44)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        Fingering weight yarn, size 4 needle\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1900 (1900, 2000, 2200, 2200, 2400, 2400)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        DK weight yarn, size US 6 circular 24” or 32” needles\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1100 (1200, 1300, 1350, 1500, 1600, 1600)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <ul>\r\n                                <li>\r\n                                    <span>\r\n                                        Worsted weight yarn, size 7 needle\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                </li>\r\n                            </ul>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Yardage needed:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1300 (1400, 1500, 1600, 1600, 1700, 1700)\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n            <p id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n        <div class="col-md-12" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n            <h2>\r\n                <strong>\r\n                    Directions:\r\n                </strong>\r\n            </h2>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Using a circular needle 2 sizes smaller than the needle used to get gauge, cast on&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON]]&nbsp;stitches.\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Join in the round, being careful not to twist the stitches.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Work in a knit 1, purl 1 rib for&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    [[LENGTH_OF_RIBBING]] inches.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    Change to the needle size used to get gauge. Begin knitting in pattern, placing markers as follows:\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    *Knit [[NO_STITCHES_BETWEEN_PATTERN]],&nbsp;\r\n                </span>\r\n                <span>\r\n                    pm, p1, k1, p1, k1, p1, pm* 5 times. Place a different marker to indicate halfway around. Repeat this pattern once, and place a different marker to indicate the beginning of the round.\r\n                </span>\r\n            </p>\r\n            <table>\r\n                <tbody>\r\n                    <tr>\r\n                        <td>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                inches from the lower edge to the underarm.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <h3>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Neckline Shaping\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h3>\r\n                            <h4>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Front\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue to knit the front in pattern.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Shape armholes as follows:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Decrease 1 stitch at each end\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                times as follows:\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. At the same time, place a marker at the center.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    2nd row: Purl back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Turn. Put right front shoulder stitches on a holder.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <b>\r\n                                    Left Front Shaping:\r\n                                </b>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Continue to shape the v-neck while knitting straight at the armhole edge:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl to the armhole edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit to 3 stitches from the end, ssk, k1.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl to the armhole edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit straight at armhole edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge every other row until there are&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches remaining and the armhole depth equals\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                inches.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]] stitches at the&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    beginning of the next right side row.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at the&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    beginning of the next row.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <b>\r\n                                    Right Front Shaping:\r\n                                </b>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Place right front stitches back on the needle and&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    attach yarn to the right side at the neck edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Shape neckline as follows:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    K1, k2tog, knit to the end.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl to the neck edge.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge every other row until there are\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches remaining.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit straight until armhole depth measures [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches at\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    the beginning of the next wrong side row.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                the beginning of the next row.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <h4>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Back\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Place the back stitches on the needle. Continue to knit the back in pattern while shaping the armholes as follows:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Decrease 1 stitch at each end\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                times as follows:\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. At the same time, place a marker at the center.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Purl back.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Knit straight until armhole depth equals\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                inches.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_3]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off center stitches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <h3>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Sleeves\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h3>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Cast on&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                [[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON_FOR_SLEEVE]]\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    stitches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    K2, p2 rib for 8 rows.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Begin stockinette stitch.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[TEXT_FOR_FOREARM_INCREASES]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[TEXT_FOR_UPPER_ARM_INCREASES]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Knit straight until the sleeve measures [[ARM_LENGTH_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <h4>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Sleeve Cap Shaping:\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h4>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                Bind off\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    &nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;\r\n                                </span>\r\n                                at the beginning of the next 2 rows.\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Decrease 1 each side every other row [[DEC_1_STITCH_EVERY_OTHER_ROW_X_TIMES]] times.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off 2 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_2_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off 4 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_4_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    [[BO_REMAINING_1]]\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <h3>\r\n                                <strong>\r\n                                    Finishing\r\n                                </strong>\r\n                            </h3>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Sew the front and back together at the shoulders. Starting at shoulder, pick up and knit an even number of stitches at the rate of about [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches per inch around the neck, placing a marker at the center front.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Work a knit 1, purl 1 rib for [[LENGTH_OF_NECK_EDGE_RIBBING]] inches around the neck as follows:\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Beginning at the shoulder, knit in rib to 2 stitches before the front center v marker, k2tog, sm, p, sm, ssk, knit in rib to beginning of round.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Bind off loosely. Sew the side and sleeve seams.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Pin the sleeves into the armhole, lining up the top of the sleeve cap with the shoulder seam and the underarm seams of the sleeve and the sweater. Sew the armhole in, easing curve of the sleeve cap as you sew.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                            <p>\r\n                                <span>\r\n                                    Weave in all loose ends.\r\n                                </span>\r\n                            </p>\r\n                        </td>\r\n                    </tr>\r\n                </tbody>\r\n            </table>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>', '<div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" id="8a10-e0b8-a0fc-e106" style="display: block; position: relative; opacity: 1; left: 0px; top: 0px;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526132035Untitled drawing (28).jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="6272-66f2-1ecb-e36f" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" id="7d9e-9c22-d7b6-f85f" style="display: block; position: relative; opacity: 1; left: 0px; top: 0px;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="459a-0946-826e-7e2d"><h2 style="text-align: center;">Trevor’s V-Necked Sweater</h2>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Design by Jane Nickerson</h4></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="image" id="1402-20e1-ddda-3b9b" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-picture-o fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Image</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <img src="https://s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/knitfitcoall/knitfit/products/1526562110Trevor and Angel.jpg" class="img-responsive" title="default title" id="efa6-45f5-0c31-7584" rel="" style="width: 100%; height: auto;">\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="639f-d0f6-5da1-3cd2">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="743a-4e3e-3de4-86fb"><h2><strong>Description:</strong></h2>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>If he’s anything like mine, your son wants a comfortable, no fuss sweater. This is a true classic, with just enough pattern to make it an interesting but not complicated knit. The pattern is written for standard sizing plus one inch of ease for a relaxed fit. If your guy is a “Hipster”, you might try a “Shapely Fit” for a tighter sweater. However, you can specify “Casual” for a more loose fit.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3><strong>Sizes:</strong></h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>This sweater has been created for you, [[FIRST_NAME]] [[LAST_NAME]], with your measurements.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3><strong>Gauge:</strong></h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>This pattern has been written for a gauge of [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches and [[ROW_GAUGE]] rows per inch.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>The original design was created in a gauge of 4 stitches and 5 rows per inch in stockinette. However, you can select a yarn from fingering to aran weight if you’d like. Just make sure that you have knit an accurate gauge swatch in the yarn you will be using.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Note: To measure a proper gauge, cast on 40 stitches using the needle size recommended for the yarn. Knit in Stockinette for at least 4 inches. Take swatch off the needles, lay it flat and measure in the center towards the top of the swatch. Knit using suggested needles first. Adjust needle size until you have a swatch that feels soft and drapey without being too loose.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="2930-1269-dc86-3405">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="4a8b-12be-9c66-91e2"><h3 id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526"><strong>Materials:</strong></h3>\r\n<table id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>1 - 24 or 32” Circular needle in the size used to knit the gauge swatch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>1 - 24 or 32” Circular needle in the size 2 sizes smaller than that used to knit the gauge swatch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>8 - stitch markers</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2 - stitch markers different from the 8 for side markers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Yarn estimated for sizes 32 (34, 36, 38, 40, 42, 44)</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Fingering weight yarn, size 4 needle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span>Yardage needed:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>1900 (1900, 2000, 2200, 2200, 2400, 2400)</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>DK weight yarn, size US 6 circular 24” or 32” needles</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span>Yardage needed:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>1100 (1200, 1300, 1350, 1500, 1600, 1600)</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Worsted weight yarn, size 7 needle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span>Yardage needed:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>1300 (1400, 1500, 1600, 1600, 1700, 1700)</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526"></p>\r\n<table id="4c24-b095-2ff2-e526">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr></tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div><div class="lyrow ui-draggable" style="display: block;">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon-remove glyphicon"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info btn-xs clone"><i class="fa fa-clone"></i></a>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview"><input type="text" value="12" class="form-control"></div>\r\n                                    <div class="view">\r\n                                        <div class="row clearfix" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px -15px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);">\r\n                                            <div class="col-md-12 column ui-sortable" style="padding: 39px 19px 24px; margin: 0px; background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"><div class="box box-element ui-draggable active" data-type="paragraph" style="display: block;" id="4bbc-7ff6-e74e-5a44">\r\n                                    <a href="#close" class="remove btn btn-danger btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></i></a>\r\n                                    <a class="drag btn btn-default btn-xs"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-move"></i></a>\r\n                                    <span class="configuration">\r\n                                        <a class="btn btn-xs btn-warning settings" href="#"><i class="fa fa-gear"></i></a>\r\n                                    </span>\r\n\r\n                                    <div class="preview">\r\n                                        <i class="fa fa-font fa-2x"></i>\r\n                                        <div class="element-desc">Paragraph</div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div class="view" id="1d3a-92c6-f9c3-0d6e"><h2><strong>Directions:</strong></h2>\r\n<p><span>Using a circular needle 2 sizes smaller than the needle used to get gauge, cast on&nbsp;</span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON]]&nbsp;stitches.</p>\r\n<p><span>Join in the round, being careful not to twist the stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Work in a knit 1, purl 1 rib for&nbsp;</span><span>[[LENGTH_OF_RIBBING]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>Change to the needle size used to get gauge. Begin knitting in pattern, placing markers as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><span>*Knit [[NO_STITCHES_BETWEEN_PATTERN]],&nbsp;</span><span>pm, p1, k1, p1, k1, p1, pm* 5 times. Place a different marker to indicate halfway around. Repeat this pattern once, and place a different marker to indicate the beginning of the round.</span></p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span>Knit in stockinette until the sweater measures [[LOWER_EDGE_TO_UNDER_ARM]]&nbsp;</span>inches from the lower edge to the underarm.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h3><strong>Neckline Shaping</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>Front</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the holder, and continue to knit the front in pattern.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Shape armholes as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;</span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>1st row: K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. At the same time, place a marker at the center.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>2nd row: Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Turn. Put right front shoulder stitches on a holder.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><b>Left Front Shaping:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Continue to shape the v-neck while knitting straight at the armhole edge:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit to 3 stitches from the end, ssk, k1.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight at armhole edge.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge every other row until there are&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]</span>stitches remaining and the armhole depth equals<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;</span>inches.</p>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]] stitches at the&nbsp;</span><span>beginning of the next right side row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at the&nbsp;</span><span>beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><b>Right Front Shaping:</b></p>\r\n<p><span>Place right front stitches back on the needle and&nbsp;</span><span>attach yarn to the right side at the neck edge.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Shape neckline as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>K1, k2tog, knit to the end.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl to the neck edge.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Continue to shape neckline, decreasing at the neck edge every other row until there are<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_AT_SHOULDER]]&nbsp;</span>stitches remaining.</p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight until armhole depth measures [[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at<span>&nbsp;</span><span>the beginning of the next wrong side row.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off [[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]] stitches at&nbsp;</span>the beginning of the next row.</p>\r\n<p><span>Knit back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off remaining stitches at the beginning of the next row.</span></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Back</strong></h4>\r\n<p><span>Place the back stitches on the needle. Continue to knit the back in pattern while shaping the armholes as follows:</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p>Decrease 1 stitch at each end<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_TIMES_TO_DECREASE_1_STITCH_AT_EACH_END]]&nbsp;</span>times as follows:</p>\r\n<p><span>K1, k2tog, knit to the last 3 stitches, ssk, k1. At the same time, place a marker at the center.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Purl back.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Knit straight until armhole depth equals<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[DEPTH_OF_ARMHOLE_BEFORE_BINDOFF]]&nbsp;</span>inches.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_1]]&nbsp;</span><span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_2]]&nbsp;</span><span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off&nbsp;</span><span>[[SHOULDER_BIND_OFF_3]]&nbsp;</span><span>stitches at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Bind off center stitches.</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Sleeves</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Cast on&nbsp;</span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_TO_CAST_ON_FOR_SLEEVE]]<span>&nbsp;</span><span>stitches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>K2, p2 rib for 8 rows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Begin stockinette stitch.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_FOREARM_INCREASES]]</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>[[TEXT_FOR_UPPER_ARM_INCREASES]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Knit straight until the sleeve measures [[ARM_LENGTH_TO_UNDER_ARM]] inches.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h4><strong>Sleeve Cap Shaping:</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Bind off [[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_FIRST_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]] at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p>Bind off<span>&nbsp;</span><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_SECOND_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]&nbsp;</span>at the beginning of the next 2 rows.</p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_THIRD_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[NO_OF_STITCHES_FOR_4TH_DECREASE_AT_ARMHOLE]]</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Decrease 1 each side every other row [[DEC_1_STITCH_EVERY_OTHER_ROW_X_TIMES]] times.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 2 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_2_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off 4 at the beginning of the next two rows [[BO_4_STITCHES_BEG_NEXT_X_ROWS]] times.</span></p>\r\n<p><span>[[BO_REMAINING_1]]</span></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Finishing</strong></h3>\r\n<p><span>Sew the front and back together at the shoulders. Starting at shoulder, pick up and knit an even number of stitches at the rate of about [[STITCH_GAUGE]] stitches per inch around the neck, placing a marker at the center front.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Work a knit 1, purl 1 rib for [[LENGTH_OF_NECK_EDGE_RIBBING]] inches around the neck as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Beginning at the shoulder, knit in rib to 2 stitches before the front center v marker, k2tog, sm, p, sm, ssk, knit in rib to beginning of round.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Bind off loosely. Sew the side and sleeve seams.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Pin the sleeves into the armhole, lining up the top of the sleeve cap with the shoulder seam and the underarm seams of the sleeve and the sweater. Sew the armhole in, easing curve of the sleeve cap as you sew.</span></p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p><span>Weave in all loose ends.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table></div>\r\n                                </div></div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>', NULL, NULL, NULL);
